Prose-feasibility audit. At each passage below, the listed world-states may be
active when the player arrives. A writer can honor at most {{ cap }} states in one
passage. For each passage, decide which states its prose should NOT address —
states that are true but irrelevant to this scene ("don't mention the romance in
the vault heist"). What you leave relevant, the writer must honor.

VISION: {{ vision.genre }}, {{ vision.tone }}.

PASSAGES:
{% for p in passages %}
- {{ p.passage.id }}: {{ p.passage.summary }}
  possibly active:
{% for flag, text in p.active %}
  - {{ flag }}: {{ text }}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

REQUIREMENTS:
- One entry per passage above: {"passage": id, "irrelevant": [flag ids]}. An empty
  list means every active state matters in that scene.
- Mark a state irrelevant only when the scene genuinely doesn't touch it — the
  audit is about honesty, not budget. But where more than {{ cap }} states are
  active, you MUST bring the relevant count within {{ cap }}.
- A state that the passage's own beats grant or directly pay off is never
  irrelevant there.
